      "summary": "Collector failures can silently erase in-memory urbit state during broadcast ticks.",
      "related_files": [
        "goseg/broadcast/loop.go",
        "goseg/broadcast/collectors/collectors.go"
      ],
      "evidence": [
        "In `runBroadcastTickWithRuntime` (goseg/broadcast/loop.go), when `constructPierInfoFn()` returns an error, the function logs and returns `pierInfo` from a nil-safe empty map path rather than preserving or reconciling prior state.",
        "This behavior sends a broadcast update with no pier entries for that tick, effectively downgrading known state to unknown."
      ],
      "suggestion": "On collector error, keep previous `pierInfo` and merge in successful deltas only, or skip publishing that tick; emit structured telemetry and return an explicit degraded-state indicator instead of replacing state with an empty map.",
